 Taco Mac BREWNIVERSITY!\nMenu Main\nWings\nWings\nOriginal\n40 Cal Per Wing\nOrder online\nOven Roasted\n40 Cal Per Wing\nOrder online\nBoneless\n70 Cal Per Wing\nOrder online\nPick Your Style\nOriginal / Roasted\n6\n6-PACK\n$9.49\n10\nSINGLE\n$14.99\n20\nDOUBLE\n$25.99\n30\nTRIPLE\n$36.99\n50\nPARTY\n$59.99\nBoneless\n6\n6-PACK\n$8.99\n10\nSINGLE\n$12.99\n20\nDOUBLE\n$22.99\n30\nTRIPLE\n$33.99\n50\nPARTY\n$54.99\nOur original wings are naturally raised, American Humane Certified and 100% antibiotic-free.\nPick Your Flavor\nClassic\nMild Buffalo\n30 Cal\nMedium Buffalo\nHot Buffalo\nThree Mile Island\n10 Cal\nCajun Voodoo Magic\n10 Cal\nSlow Burn\n10 Cal\nDry Rubs\nOriginal Lemon Pepper\n10 Cal\nButtermilk Ranch\n10 Cal\nSweet Heat\nAsian Sweet Heat\n20 Cal\nSweet Sesame Ginger\n20 Cal\nHoney Chipotle\n10 Cal\nSpicy Mango\n20 Cal\nHot Honey Mustard\n20 Cal\nHabanero BBQ\n20 Cal\nMild Classics\nParmesan Garlic\n60 Cal\nWet Lemon Pepper\n40 Cal\nBBQ\n10 Cal\nBites & Shares\nBites & Shares\nFried Mushrooms\nHand-battered button mushrooms, served with creamy horseradish sauce.\n650 Cal\n$8.99\nCrispy Brussel Sprouts\nWith honey drizzle.\n260 Cal\n$8.99\nSpinach Dip\nServed with chips and Salsa.\n1190 Cal\n$8.99\nTrio Dip\nQueso dip, guacamole, and salsa, served with chips and flour tortillas.\n1590 Cal\n$10.99\nChips and Housemade Salsa\nHousemade chips and salsa, made fresh daily.\n460 Cal\n$4.99\nFried Pickle Chips\nHand-battered dill pickle chips, served with housemade ranch.\n880 Cal\n$6.49\nQueso Dip\nQueso topped with cheddar jack cheese and pickled jalapenos, served with salsa, chips, and flour tortillas.\nSm. 780 Cal. or Lg. 1040 Cal. Cal\nSmall\n780 Cal\n$6.99\nLarge\n1040 Cal\n$8.99\nMozzarella Sticks\nGolden brown cheesy goodness, served with warm marinara sauce.\n770 Cal\n$8.99\nBavarian Pretzel Bites\nServed with housemade queso and honey mustard.\n1210 Cal\n$8.99\nTrain Wreck Nachos\nQueso, pico de gallo, fresh jalapenos, white onions, cheddar jack. Served with salsa, chips, flour tortillas, and sour cream. Add Guac +$1.00\nGround Beef\n2320 Cal\n$12.99\nChicken Tinga\n2280 Cal\n$12.99\nPhilly Egg Roll\nThinly sliced steak, queso, sauteed onions, and peppers - in a hand-wrapped egg roll, served with our signature '79 sauce.\n550 Cal\n$7.99\nJalapeño Bacon Cheddar Egg Roll\nJalapeños, bacon, cheddar, cream cheese, and green onions, in a hand-wrapped egg roll, served with housemade chipotle crema.\n1500 Cal\n$7.99\nLoaded Guacamole\nGuacamole with Mexican street corn, queso fresco, pico de gallo, pickled red onions, cilantro, and Tajin, served with chips.\n670 Cal\n$9.49\nBurgers\nBur\n\n--- Page: /about ---\nThe Taco Mac Restaurants Story\nFind your\nLocation\nFind nearest location\n,\nSee Location\nMenu\nOrder Online\nCatering\nBrewniversity\nLocations\nMore from\nTaco Mac\nAbout Taco Mac\nPress\nGift Cards\nCareers\nContact Us\nTeam Members\nPrivacy Policy\nMenu\nCatering\nLocations\nBrewniversity\nOrder online\nJoin e-club\nAbout Taco Mac\nPress\nGift Cards\nCareers\nContact Us\nTeam Members\nPrivacy Policy\nBREWNIVERSITY SIGN-UP\nDedicated to the exploration and enjoyment of delicious, unique and rare craft beers.\nWelcome to the Taco Mac BREWNIVERSITY!\nAbout Taco Mac\nHeaded South\nIt all started back in 1979 when a couple of guys from Buffalo, NY, made a pit stop in Atlanta on their way to Florida. After touring the city and enjoying the weather, they decided to stay and bring their favorite food, buffalo wings, to the sunny South.\nAbout Those Tacos…\nThe perfect location was found, but with limited funds remaining, a decision had to be made – renovate the kitchen or change the sign out front? The kitchen won and the Mexican-Irish-sounding name, Taco Mac, remained. Before long, other Buffalo natives came down to help the guys introduce Atlanta to Buffalo-style chicken wings.\nHmmm, What Goes With Wings?\nAs the popularity of Taco Mac buffalo wings increased, cold beer and sports seemed like natural partners. The wall of drafts grew to offer the largest selection of microbrewed beers and imports in the South – decades before anyone was pouring “craft” beers. It quickly became a hot spot among the locals.\nStill Wingin’ It\nForty years later, we’ve grown a lot, opening locations all over Georgia and as far away as and Tennessee. And we’ve also gone way beyond wings to make sure our kitchen serves everyone’s favorite foods – big, juicy burgers, hand-breaded chicken tenders, sandwiches, fresh entrée salads and tacos, of course. But we still serve the Southeast’s original and award-winning Buffalo Wings, offer the best selection of craft beers on draft and bring you the friendliest Southern hospitality we fell in love with so many years ago.\nClosest Location\nSwitch Location\nConyers\nMacon\nPelham\nDawsonville\nGainesville\nHiram\nLawrenceville\nSuwanee\nPeachtree City\nNewnan\nMarietta\nKennesaw\nJohns Creek\nDuluth\nDouglasville\nCumming\nCumberland\nCrabapple\nCanton\nOld Milton\nPrado\nWindward\nWoodstock\nMall of Georgia\nPerimeter\nMcDonough\nOrder Online\nView Menu\nJoin E-Club\nMiles Away!\nMore details\nOn Tap:",
